author: Dan Price Guest columnist
title: Bluegrass Skies: The year in space | Spectrum | state-journal.com
text:
It’s been another incredible year in space exploration. Humanity continued to push the boundaries of our understanding by peering deeper into the Universe than ever before. We also pursued the mysteries of our own origins, while searching for conditions suitable for life on other planets and moons in our own solar system and beyond.
Dan Price
The James Webb Space Telescope (JWST), a joint mission of NASA, the Canadian Space Agency and the European Space Agency (ESA) celebrated one year of operation in July 2023. JWST returned striking new images of the four giant planets of our solar system — Uranus, Neptune, Saturn and Jupiter.
